Read in data / data cleaning

dat<-read.csv("stroke.csv")

# left with 3425 observations
dat<-dat|> filter(gender!="Other", bmi!="N/A", smoking_status!="Unknown")

Create training and test sets

set.seed(1)
test_index <- createDataPartition(dat$stroke,times=1,p=0.2,list=FALSE)
test_set <- dat[test_index,]
train_set <-dat[-test_index,]

Sample charateristic in test set

a=sum(test_set$stroke==0)
b=sum(test_set$stroke==1)

# Gender
gen<- test_set|> 
        group_by(gender,stroke)|>
        summarise(count=n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'gender'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
gen|>mutate(percentage=case_when(
  stroke==0~count/(a),
  stroke==1~count/(b)))|>
  ggplot(aes(stroke,percentage,fill=gender))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity",alpha=0.5)+
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c(0,1))+
  ggtitle("Stroke vs. Gender")

# Age
test_set|>
  ggplot(aes(x=age,fill=factor(stroke)))+
  geom_histogram(alpha=0.5,binwidth = 6)+
  ggtitle("Stroke vs. Age")

# Hypertension
hyper<- test_set|> 
        group_by(hypertension,stroke)|>
        summarise(count=n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'hypertension'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
hyper|>mutate(percentage=case_when(
  stroke==0~count/(a),
  stroke==1~count/(b)))|>
  ggplot(aes(stroke,percentage,fill=hypertension))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity",alpha=0.5)+
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c(0,1))+
  ggtitle("Stroke vs. Hypertension")
